<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
<tr>
	<td width="1%">&nbsp;</td>
	<td width="98%">
	
		<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">
		<tr>

		
			<tr>
				<td><font face="verdana" size="1">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<a href="/quests/default.asp">Quests</a><br>
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tline.gif">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<a href="default.asp?land=1375">Everfrost</a><br>
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tline3.gif">
				<img src="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/open.gif">&nbsp;<b>Elixir Delivery</b><br><br>
				</td>
			</tr>
				
			<tr>
			<td>
				<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="3"><b>    Elixir Delivery</b>&nbsp;<a href="../Subscribe.asp?DID=23733"><font face="Verdana" size="2">[Subscribe to this document]</font></a></font>
					<br>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">
					<b><a href="mailto:n.tscheligi@mailcity.com">Ravenflight</a> | 
		                        1/1/2000 12:22:05 PM</b></font></p>
					
					<p>
					<font face="verdana" size="2">You get this quest from the first warrior outside the Pit of Doom in Halas (the one in silver armor with two swords). Follow the keywords and he'll give you a bottle that you carry around to four warriors around Everfrost mountains. You'll get exp and faction improvements with the warriors and shamans at each step. The last person to get the bottle is Megan out in the Tundra, so if you're young I suggest you look for company for this step: nasty MOBs hanging around there sometimes (orc shamans and the like).<BR>
<BR>
Return the empty bottle to the guy at the Pit of Doom and get a few coppers and a weapon.<BR>
<BR>
Nice little quest.
			<br>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></p>
					</p>
			</td>
			</tr>
