	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				At low levels I completed this quest many times, not once did I use Snowflake to get to Meghan.  I have completed this quest with a 2nd level.  The first guard is very easy to find, the second is by snowflake if I remember correctly. Go down the ramp, out the pass and turn left, at the large open space (a good place to camp at about lv.4) go left again. This should take you to the three guards and snowflake. From here head back to the open space. Staying on the walls turn left again (very bumpy going at first) when you reach the next Y go left again, at the next Y go right, then left.  Follow this and you will come to a large cave opening. This is BlackBorrow, and the third guard stands near a tree in this clearing.  If he isn't here he will be back. Reverse yourself to get back to Snowflake, follow her if you wish, or just follow the wall around to the left, you will come to a large ruined temple, behind the temple is a snow ridge.  Run along this ridge untill you see the tower.  If Meghan is not there, wait, she will return.  Good luck and safe paths to you!
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
